<br>
But Skylar being every so curious was not too upset about it.. yet. He was up and ready to go and once he heard that knock on the door, he ran over to open it. Once seeing Yakut the young boy jumped up and down in excitment. He hugged onto his aunt yelling &quot;Ready to go?! Ready to go?!&quot; <br>
<br>
Shyriana stepped up to the door with a weak smile. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hello.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenyakut>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen Shamaness</span><br>  Posts: 326<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/16/03 5:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/magickalamzn/images/yakut1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A challenge.</span><hr size=1> A smile caressed her features, as she bent down to her nephew's level. Yakut placed her hand on his shoulder, softly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good Morning, Skylar. Yes, I am ready.&quot;, she stood up and looked into Shyriana's deep green eyes. She knew how this felt. When Glory went to XVH with Isabelle to visit, Yakut went crazy. She'd speak in visions to Glory and Isabelle so much they were sometimes confused.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know, believe me I know. You'll want to just run out and take him back into your arms of protection. Try your best not to worry, He's with me. I'll contact you through visions at a routine time.&quot; she smiled hoping this gave some comfort.<br>
<br>
